01:01:47,242 --> 01:01:50,142
(<i> bell and drum stop</i> )

804
01:02:13,399 --> 01:02:16,729
(<i> chains rattling</i> )

805
01:02:23,574 --> 01:02:26,774
(<i> crowd murmuring</i> )

806
01:02:29,278 --> 01:02:31,478
WOMAN:
Stir the tiles!

807
01:02:31,480 --> 01:02:33,780
(<i> crowd chanting</i> ):
Stir the tiles!

808
01:02:33,783 --> 01:02:37,623
Stir the tiles!

809
01:02:37,619 --> 01:02:40,049
Stir the tiles!

810
01:02:44,624 --> 01:02:47,894
(<i> crowd chanting</i> ):
Draw the name!

811
01:02:47,893 --> 01:02:49,633
Draw the name!

812
01:02:49,628 --> 01:02:53,758
(<i> chanting continues</i> )

813
01:03:03,106 --> 01:03:06,936
HORSRIK:
Now, my countrymen, hear me.

814
01:03:06,943 --> 01:03:10,683
Behold, for I am chosen.

815
01:03:10,679 --> 01:03:13,249
I shall die that many may live.

816
01:03:13,248 --> 01:03:18,018
I shall lay down my life
for family and fellows.

817
01:03:18,018 --> 01:03:22,848
I shall go to my grave
for the love of our king

818
01:03:22,856 --> 01:03:29,086
and his wise policy,
and my name is...

819
01:03:37,502 --> 01:03:38,902
WOMAN:
Read the name!

820
01:03:38,903 --> 01:03:40,473
CROWD:
Read the name!

821
01:03:40,471 --> 01:03:43,971
(<i> crowd clamoring</i> )

822
01:03:46,608 --> 01:03:50,278
(<i> crowd shouting</i> ):
Read the name!

823
01:03:53,447 --> 01:03:55,177
(<i> crowd quiets</i> )

824
01:03:55,182 --> 01:03:58,352
Read the name.

825
01:04:01,052 --> 01:04:06,152
The name is...
Princess Elspeth

826
01:04:06,156 --> 01:04:07,416
Ophelus.

827
01:04:07,423 --> 01:04:08,693
(<i> crowd gasping and murmuring</i> )

828
01:04:08,691 --> 01:04:11,361
Clearly outrageous.

829
01:04:11,359 --> 01:04:14,029
That is not the name;
it has been misread.

830
01:04:14,029 --> 01:04:15,129
There's no mistake.

831
01:04:15,130 --> 01:04:16,700
The name's been drawn.

832
01:04:16,698 --> 01:04:19,398
Let it stand!

833
01:04:19,399 --> 01:04:22,099
No. The good Horsrik
has misspoke himself.

834
01:04:22,102 --> 01:04:23,772
In fairness to
this individual,

835
01:04:23,770 --> 01:04:25,570
whose name I
can't make out,

836
01:04:25,571 --> 01:04:27,001
we will destroy
this tile.

837
01:04:27,005 --> 01:04:28,665
(<i> scattered shouts of "No!"</i> )

838
01:04:28,673 --> 01:04:31,113
What better name
than your own kin?

839
01:04:31,108 --> 01:04:33,578
At last we see justice done.

840
01:04:33,577 --> 01:04:34,507
Silence!

841
01:04:34,511 --> 01:04:37,511
We will have
a new choosing.

842
01:04:37,514 --> 01:04:40,454
I will draw
the name myself.

843
01:04:40,450 --> 01:04:42,180
VALERIAN:
Let it stand!

844
01:04:42,185 --> 01:04:44,785
Let it stand!
Let it stand!

845
01:04:44,787 --> 01:04:48,387
(<i> crowd shouting</i> ):
Let it stand!

846
01:04:50,758 --> 01:04:54,888
The name
is as Horsrik read it...

847
01:04:57,196 --> 01:04:59,626
Elspeth.

848
01:05:02,200 --> 01:05:05,870
CASIODORUS REX:
This one, this
one, another,

849
01:05:05,869 --> 01:05:08,999
another...
another...

850
01:05:09,005 --> 01:05:09,995
and another.

851
01:05:10,006 --> 01:05:12,506
What treachery
is this?

852
01:05:12,508 --> 01:05:14,568
The lottery is invalid.

853
01:05:14,576 --> 01:05:15,976
Hear me, good people.

854
01:05:15,977 --> 01:05:19,977
It is true that my name
appears on all the lots.

855
01:05:19,980 --> 01:05:23,710
This does not
invalidate the lottery.

856
01:05:23,716 --> 01:05:25,546
It certifies it.

857
01:05:25,551 --> 01:05:28,291
It redresses
an injustice.

858
01:05:28,287 --> 01:05:29,247
I have learnt

859
01:05:29,254 --> 01:05:31,654
that my name has been
kept from jeopardy

860
01:05:31,656 --> 01:05:33,216
in all the drawings

861
01:05:33,224 --> 01:05:34,824
in the past.

862
01:05:34,825 --> 01:05:36,425
Therefore, I
have substituted

863
01:05:36,427 --> 01:05:40,097
my name for yours,

864
01:05:40,096 --> 01:05:43,756
for the risk that over the years
you have taken and I have not.

865
01:05:43,767 --> 01:05:47,537
(<i> crowd murmuring</i> )

866
01:06:12,561 --> 01:06:15,561
(<i> items clattering</i> )

867
01:06:37,652 --> 01:06:39,082
You... Tyrian...

868
01:06:39,086 --> 01:06:41,086
surely you'll
do something.

869
01:06:41,088 --> 01:06:42,618
If not for me...

870
01:06:42,622 --> 01:06:44,722
out of loyalty
to the kingdom.

871
01:06:44,724 --> 01:06:47,094
But that's just it,
Your Majesty.

872
01:06:47,093 --> 01:06:51,993
My first duty is...
loyalty to the kingdom.

873
01:06:54,298 --> 01:06:56,968
Don't go to all that trouble.

874
01:06:59,402 --> 01:07:00,892
I'm unarmed!

875
01:07:00,886 --> 01:07:02,366
If you want to fight,
at least give me a weapon.

876
01:07:02,371 --> 01:07:03,401
I think not!

877
01:07:03,405 --> 01:07:04,595
Stop!

878
01:07:04,606 --> 01:07:07,666
Don't... harm him.

879
01:07:07,675 --> 01:07:11,705
And you, please...

880
01:07:11,711 --> 01:07:14,231
(<i> chuckling</i> )

881
01:07:14,229 --> 01:07:16,749
I've always had the greatest
admiration for the black arts--

882
01:07:16,748 --> 01:07:20,518
you chaps with your...
mysterious

883
01:07:20,518 --> 01:07:22,328
spells.

884
01:07:22,335 --> 01:07:24,145
I didn't think it
would be necessary.

885
01:07:24,154 --> 01:07:25,754
Vermithrax is
an old dragon,

886
01:07:25,755 --> 01:07:26,865
and that, I thought,

887
01:07:26,872 --> 01:07:27,992
was the beauty
of my plan...

888
01:07:27,990 --> 01:07:29,720
(<i> rueful chuckle</i> )

889
01:07:29,725 --> 01:07:30,555
...time.

890
01:07:30,559 --> 01:07:32,489
We'd wait it out.

891
01:07:32,493 --> 01:07:34,433
I'd live to see
the end of it.

892
01:07:37,364 --> 01:07:38,204
I will

893
01:07:38,198 --> 01:07:40,228
see the end of it.

894
01:07:40,233 --> 01:07:43,933
Sire, I beg you consider
what you are doing.

895
01:07:43,936 --> 01:07:45,836
Give him that,
he'll destroy

896
01:07:45,837 --> 01:07:47,767
everything
you've built.

897
01:07:47,772 --> 01:07:50,072
He shall have it.

898
01:07:50,074 --> 01:07:52,914
It... it's my daughter.

899
01:07:52,910 --> 01:07:56,280
Save her, I beg you.

900
01:08:15,364 --> 01:08:19,004
That princess...
what's her name?

901
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:20,970
She surprised me.

902
01:08:20,968 --> 01:08:22,698
Elspeth.

903
01:08:22,703 --> 01:08:26,073
Her name's Elspeth.

904
01:08:26,073 --> 01:08:29,143
There. Good and hot.

905
01:08:29,142 --> 01:08:33,642
That's not the kind of fire
we need.

906
01:08:38,216 --> 01:08:44,416
(<i> reciting spell</i>
<i> in Latin</i> )

907
01:08:53,396 --> 01:08:56,756
(<i> humming vibration</i> )

908
01:09:00,102 --> 01:09:03,142
(<i> clinking</i> )

909
01:09:03,737 --> 01:09:07,267
(<i> clanging</i> )

910
01:09:22,053 --> 01:09:24,723
Good. Now
turn it over.

911
01:09:24,722 --> 01:09:27,322
(<i> clanging continues</i> )

912
01:10:20,676 --> 01:10:25,876
(<i> stones clattering underfoot</i> )

913
01:10:48,236 --> 01:10:50,166
(<i> snarling</i> )

914
01:10:50,171 --> 01:10:54,941
(<i> metal clinking</i>
<i> and fire sizzling</i> )

915
01:10:56,475 --> 01:11:00,805
An edge like no
other on this earth.

916
01:11:08,652 --> 01:11:11,892
I'll say good-bye
to her for you.

917
01:11:11,888 --> 01:11:14,318
I'm sorry
she's not here.

918
01:11:14,323 --> 01:11:16,163
You know how she is.

919
01:11:16,158 --> 01:11:18,858
I understand.

920
01:11:20,828 --> 01:11:23,828
Fare thee well.

921
01:11:24,298 --> 01:11:26,968
(<i> sighs</i> )

922
01:11:30,936 --> 01:11:35,836
(<i> raptor calling</i> )

923
01:11:39,109 --> 01:11:41,309
VALERIAN:
It's a shield.

924
01:11:41,311 --> 01:11:42,781
I made it.

925
01:11:42,779 --> 01:11:47,309
It might keep the fire
off you; it might not.

926
01:11:47,948 --> 01:11:50,108
You know,
you're an idiot.

927
01:11:50,116 --> 01:11:52,446
You're going
to die tonight.

928
01:11:52,451 --> 01:11:54,751
You'll be ripped
limb from limb.

929
01:11:54,753 --> 01:11:59,353
This is the last time
I'll ever speak to you.

930
01:12:01,791 --> 01:12:02,791
Thank you.

931
01:12:02,792 --> 01:12:05,092
Another thing.

932
01:12:05,094 --> 01:12:08,034
I've been up there.

933
01:12:08,030 --> 01:12:10,460
That thing isn't alone.

934
01:12:10,465 --> 01:12:12,725
It's got little ones.

935
01:12:12,733 --> 01:12:14,003
Young, I think.

936
01:12:14,000 --> 01:12:15,300
I don't know
how many.

937
01:12:15,301 --> 01:12:17,731
They'll have to be killed, too.

938
01:12:17,736 --> 01:12:19,996
Anything else?

939
01:12:27,377 --> 01:12:30,477
You're in love,
aren't you?

940
01:12:31,881 --> 01:12:34,881
Yes.

941
01:12:36,951 --> 01:12:39,151
It's all right.

942
01:12:39,154 --> 01:12:42,094
I understand.

943
01:12:42,090 --> 01:12:44,890
She's very beautiful.

944
01:12:44,892 --> 01:12:46,462
Very brave.

945
01:12:46,460 --> 01:12:49,030
Who is? What do you mean?

946
01:12:49,029 --> 01:12:51,799
Your princess.

947
01:12:54,133 --> 01:12:57,503
But I don't care.

948
01:12:59,704 --> 01:13:07,314
Listen to me, Galen Brandwardyn,
sorcerer's apprentice.

949
01:13:07,311 --> 01:13:10,181
You're going to be dead...

950
01:13:10,180 --> 01:13:13,250
the dragon
will be worse than ever,

951
01:13:13,249 --> 01:13:16,719
there will be more lotteries...

952
01:13:16,719 --> 01:13:18,589
and I'm not a boy anymore.

953
01:13:18,587 --> 01:13:21,047
And you'll be eligible
because...

954
01:13:21,056 --> 01:13:23,856
Because I'm still a virgin.

955
01:13:40,574 --> 01:13:43,174
I<i> am</i> in love...

956
01:13:47,413 --> 01:13:50,453
...but not
with the princess.

957
01:14:31,256 --> 01:14:33,456
Your Highness.

958
01:14:43,400 --> 01:14:47,230
MAN:
Now be it known
throughout the kingdom,

959
01:14:47,236 --> 01:14:50,096
that the Princess Elspeth,

960
01:14:50,105 --> 01:14:51,735
having lawfully been chosen

961
01:14:51,739 --> 01:14:55,469
by a deed of fortune
and destiny...

962
01:15:02,649 --> 01:15:04,349
(<i> spectators murmuring</i> )

963
01:15:04,350 --> 01:15:07,050
No more smoke, I beg you.

964
01:15:07,052 --> 01:15:08,752
Begone!

965
01:15:08,753 --> 01:15:13,163
I declare these proceedings...

966
01:15:13,157 --> 01:15:16,117
...duly ordained.

967
01:15:18,026 --> 01:15:19,356
TYRIAN:
I knew

968
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:22,560
I'd find you here.

969
01:15:22,563 --> 01:15:26,503
But I'm not as sentimental
as His Majesty.

970
01:15:26,499 --> 01:15:28,169
The kingdom...

971
01:15:28,167 --> 01:15:30,167
every one of us...

972
01:15:30,169 --> 01:15:33,269
needs this sacrifice.

973
01:15:33,272 --> 01:15:37,512
If you intend to interfere...

974
01:15:37,509 --> 01:15:41,009
you'll have to kill<i> me.</i>

975
01:15:45,983 --> 01:15:47,683
I've plenty of reasons
to kill you

976
01:15:47,684 --> 01:15:51,624
that have nothing to do
with this sacrifice.

977
01:15:52,988 --> 01:15:55,958
Most impressive.

978
01:15:55,957 --> 01:15:57,417
Can you use it?

979
01:15:57,425 --> 01:15:59,155
ELSPETH:
No!

980
01:15:59,160 --> 01:16:00,260
Stop!

981
01:16:00,261 --> 01:16:01,661
Tyrian is right!

982
01:16:01,662 --> 01:16:04,002
This is our only hope.

983
01:16:10,303 --> 01:16:12,273
(<i> grunting</i> )

984
01:16:23,348 --> 01:16:26,108
(<i> rumbling</i> )

985
01:16:27,083 --> 01:16:27,783
Tyrian!

986
01:16:27,783 --> 01:16:28,953
(<i> Elspeth yells</i> )

987
01:16:28,950 --> 01:16:31,120
(<i> yells</i> )

988
01:16:31,118 --> 01:16:34,118
This is no warrior.

989
01:16:44,197 --> 01:16:46,257
Run!

990
01:16:50,769 --> 01:16:52,839
Run!

991
01:17:06,783 --> 01:17:09,283
Where are you going?!

992
01:17:13,521 --> 01:17:15,551
You failed, my friend.

993
01:17:15,556 --> 01:17:19,956
And I thank
the gods for it.

994
01:17:30,736 --> 01:17:32,596
Now prepare yourself.

995
01:17:32,604 --> 01:17:34,344
(<i> Elspeth screaming</i> )

996
01:17:34,339 --> 01:17:35,369
(<i> grunting</i> )

997
01:17:35,373 --> 01:17:36,613
(<i> groaning</i> )

998
01:17:36,607 --> 01:17:39,637
(<i> scream fades</i> )

999
01:17:48,984 --> 01:17:51,984
(<i> gasps</i> )

1000
01:17:53,387 --> 01:17:55,917
(<i> groaning</i> )

1001
01:17:57,623 --> 01:18:00,923
(<i> groans</i> )

1002
01:18:14,372 --> 01:18:18,072
(<i> water trickling</i> )

1003
01:18:18,508 --> 01:18:22,908
(<i> clanking</i> )

1004
01:18:25,147 --> 01:18:27,777
Elspeth...

1005
01:18:49,503 --> 01:18:51,303
(<i> gurgling</i> )

1006
01:18:51,304 --> 01:18:55,874
(<i> noisy chewing</i> )

1007
01:19:00,678 --> 01:19:04,178
(<i> guttural growling</i> )

1008
01:19:04,181 --> 01:19:07,251
(<i> snorting</i> )

1009
01:19:12,621 --> 01:19:14,651
(<i> screams</i> )

1010
01:19:14,656 --> 01:19:18,016
(<i> snarling</i> )

1011
01:19:20,193 --> 01:19:23,333
(<i> panting</i> )

1012
01:19:32,337 --> 01:19:35,067
(<i> snarling</i> )

1013
01:19:38,810 --> 01:19:42,540
(<i> snorting and snarling</i> )

1014
01:19:42,546 --> 01:19:44,746
(<i> grunting</i> )

1015
01:19:46,782 --> 01:19:50,282
(<i> snarling</i> )

1016
01:19:51,218 --> 01:19:53,218
(<i> grunting</i> )

1017
01:19:55,221 --> 01:19:58,491
(<i> grunting</i> )

1018
01:20:02,460 --> 01:20:04,990
(<i> panting</i> )

1019
01:20:27,250 --> 01:20:30,480
(<i> roaring</i> )

1020
01:20:38,993 --> 01:20:42,493
(<i> roaring continues</i> )

1021
01:21:02,348 --> 01:21:05,778
(<i> fire roaring</i> )

1022
01:21:23,434 --> 01:21:25,034
(<i> gasping</i> )

1023
01:21:45,989 --> 01:21:50,959
(<i> rumbling</i> )

1024
01:22:08,776 --> 01:22:12,376
(<i> fire roaring</i> )

1025
01:22:35,668 --> 01:22:39,068
(<i> snarling growl</i> )

1026
01:22:44,008 --> 01:22:47,908
(<i> snarling growl</i> )

1027
01:23:26,615 --> 01:23:30,075
(<i> roars</i> )

1028
01:23:31,820 --> 01:23:34,420
(<i> roaring</i> )

1029
01:23:38,759 --> 01:23:40,929
(<i> screeches</i> )

1030
01:23:55,941 --> 01:24:00,211
(<i> snarling growl</i> )

1031
01:24:08,118 --> 01:24:11,018
(<i> growls softly</i> )

1032
01:24:20,662 --> 01:24:21,562
(<i> rumbling</i> )

1033
01:24:21,562 --> 01:24:23,962
(<i> distant growling</i> )

1034
01:24:29,002 --> 01:24:33,072
(<i> sniffing</i> )

1035
01:24:38,010 --> 01:24:40,610
(<i> sniffing</i> )

1036
01:24:40,612 --> 01:24:43,952
(<i> growling whimper</i> )

1037
01:24:43,948 --> 01:24:47,248
(<i> low, guttural growl</i> )

1038
01:24:49,019 --> 01:24:52,619
(<i> angry screeching</i> )

1039
01:25:15,244 --> 01:25:18,714
(<i> low, hissing growl</i> )

1040
01:25:34,796 --> 01:25:37,896
(<i> grunting</i> )

1041
01:25:37,899 --> 01:25:41,069
(<i> roaring</i> )

1042
01:25:42,603 --> 01:25:43,743
(<i> grunting</i> )

1043
01:25:43,737 --> 01:25:47,597
(<i> screeching in pain</i> )

1044
01:25:50,208 --> 01:25:51,808
(<i> groans</i> )

1045
01:25:54,711 --> 01:25:57,011
(<i> hissing</i> )

1046
01:25:57,013 --> 01:25:58,653
(<i> roars</i> )

1047
01:26:04,819 --> 01:26:08,349
(<i> screeching</i> )

1048
01:26:11,624 --> 01:26:14,794
(<i> moaning</i> )

1049
01:26:18,963 --> 01:26:22,433
(<i> moaning</i> )

1050
01:26:24,134 --> 01:26:26,334
(<i> roars</i> )

1051
01:26:45,254 --> 01:26:47,924
(<i> bird squawking</i> )

1052
01:27:15,616 --> 01:27:18,416
Still alive.

1053
01:27:18,818 --> 01:27:21,388
(<i> sighs</i> )

1054
01:27:35,901 --> 01:27:40,271
You know what
we have to do.

1055
01:27:40,272 --> 01:27:43,242
We have to leave.

1056
01:27:43,908 --> 01:27:46,708
You said you loved me.

1057
01:27:47,210 --> 01:27:49,910
Is it true?

1058
01:27:52,948 --> 01:27:55,618
If it is...

1059
01:27:55,617 --> 01:27:59,887
...that's the only good
we've done.

1060
01:28:01,054 --> 01:28:04,924
Let's not lose that, too.

1061
01:28:06,758 --> 01:28:09,388
Galen?

1062
01:28:10,193 --> 01:28:11,563
She's right.

1063
01:28:11,561 --> 01:28:15,431
What kind of life
could you have here?

1064
01:28:15,430 --> 01:28:17,200
You know what I think?

1065
01:28:17,198 --> 01:28:19,928
Magic, magicians--

1066
01:28:19,934 --> 01:28:22,604
it's all fading from the world,

1067
01:28:22,603 --> 01:28:24,043
dying out.

1068
01:28:24,037 --> 01:28:27,367
That makes me happy.

1069
01:28:27,373 --> 01:28:30,713
That means the dragon
will be dying, too.

1070
01:28:34,946 --> 01:28:37,706
Valerian...

1071
01:28:37,715 --> 01:28:40,675
...something
from your father.

1072
01:28:44,520 --> 01:28:48,090
You want me
to wear this.

1073
01:28:48,089 --> 01:28:49,289
What harm could it do?

1074
01:28:49,290 --> 01:28:51,820
(<i> bird cawing</i> )

1075
01:29:09,975 --> 01:29:13,605
(<i> bell ringing</i> )

1076
01:29:30,660 --> 01:29:33,330
What is it?

1077
01:29:33,329 --> 01:29:36,599
What's the matter?

1078
01:29:42,770 --> 01:29:45,640
What is that?

1079
01:29:54,280 --> 01:29:57,480
Look.

1080
01:30:00,052 --> 01:30:01,822
VALERIAN:
At what?

1081
01:30:01,820 --> 01:30:03,520
There.

1082
01:30:03,521 --> 01:30:06,261
That old trickster.

1083
01:30:06,257 --> 01:30:08,857
The burning water...

1084
01:30:08,859 --> 01:30:11,629
lake of fire...

1085
01:30:13,029 --> 01:30:15,159
He had it planned...

1086
01:30:15,164 --> 01:30:16,664
from the beginning!

1087
01:30:16,665 --> 01:30:19,225
He knew this
was going to happen!

1088
01:30:19,234 --> 01:30:20,734
Who did?

1089
01:30:20,735 --> 01:30:21,995
What happened?

1090
01:30:22,002 --> 01:30:23,602
We've got to go back.

1091
01:30:23,603 --> 01:30:26,143
I have to talk to him.

1092
01:30:27,172 --> 01:30:30,472
Where are you going?

1093
01:30:32,976 --> 01:30:36,606
GREIL:
We can slay this dragon
with song and prayer.

1094
01:30:36,612 --> 01:30:40,312
If we can but join
together in faith,

1095
01:30:40,315 --> 01:30:42,245
we shall live,

1096
01:30:42,250 --> 01:30:46,220
and the beast
shall die.

1097
01:30:46,219 --> 01:30:47,279
Galen!

1098
01:30:47,286 --> 01:30:49,416
Stop!

1099
01:30:49,420 --> 01:30:51,550
I won't let you
kill yourself!

1100
01:30:51,556 --> 01:30:52,886
He couldn't walk.

1101
01:30:52,890 --> 01:30:54,690
He knew he couldn't
make the journey,

1102
01:30:54,691 --> 01:30:57,161
so he had us
make it for him.

1103
01:30:57,160 --> 01:30:59,890
Don't you see?

1104
01:31:03,299 --> 01:31:05,429
All right, I'm
coming, too.

1105
01:31:05,434 --> 01:31:06,334
No, you're not.

1106
01:31:06,334 --> 01:31:07,404
This is for me to do.

1107
01:31:07,401 --> 01:31:08,671
I'm not afraid.

1108
01:31:08,668 --> 01:31:12,198
After all,
I was a man.

1109
01:31:12,204 --> 01:31:15,044
Remember?

1110
01:31:17,308 --> 01:31:21,878
(<i> reciting spell in Latin</i> )

1111
01:31:21,878 --> 01:31:24,608
Stay close.

1112
01:31:25,914 --> 01:31:26,654
What's that?

1113
01:31:26,648 --> 01:31:28,148
Nothing. Come on.

1114
01:31:28,149 --> 01:31:29,179
I want to see.

1115
01:31:29,183 --> 01:31:31,153
No, you don't.

1116
01:31:33,418 --> 01:31:36,848
All right.
Wait here.

1117
01:31:45,762 --> 01:31:48,432
Galen?

1118
01:31:51,967 --> 01:31:54,667
Galen!

1119
01:31:58,939 --> 01:32:01,769
Where are you?

1120
01:32:07,046 --> 01:32:10,506
(<i> fire roaring</i> )

1121
01:32:11,415 --> 01:32:15,775
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1122
01:33:47,477 --> 01:33:51,877
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1123
01:33:59,254 --> 01:34:01,554
You're back.

1124
01:34:01,556 --> 01:34:04,486
I thank the powers
that made me.

1125
01:34:04,492 --> 01:34:06,732
Glad to see you, too.

1126
01:34:06,727 --> 01:34:09,657
You didn't bring
along anything to eat,

1127
01:34:09,663 --> 01:34:11,263
by any chance?

1128
01:34:11,264 --> 01:34:12,964
Food?

1129
01:34:12,965 --> 01:34:14,325
But come along.

1130
01:34:14,333 --> 01:34:16,233
There's much to do.

1131
01:34:16,234 --> 01:34:18,204
No, please.

1132
01:34:18,202 --> 01:34:20,642
I thought
I was a sorcerer.

1133
01:34:20,637 --> 01:34:22,137
I'm not.

1134
01:34:22,138 --> 01:34:24,068
I thought I had power.

1135
01:34:24,073 --> 01:34:24,843
I don't.

1136
01:34:24,840 --> 01:34:27,340
You said to be strong.

1137
01:34:27,342 --> 01:34:29,032
I wasn't.

1138
01:34:29,026 --> 01:34:30,706
But you were,
my boy, you were,

1139
01:34:30,712 --> 01:34:34,652
and you'll be
stronger yet.

1140
01:34:34,649 --> 01:34:37,849
Thou art baptized in
the name of the Father,

1141
01:34:37,852 --> 01:34:39,592
the Son, the Holy Ghost,

1142
01:34:39,587 --> 01:34:43,047
and may the Lord
lead us from darkness

1143
01:34:43,056 --> 01:34:45,086
and-and demons.

1144
01:34:45,091 --> 01:34:46,991
Look!

1145
01:34:46,992 --> 01:34:49,932
(<i> roaring</i> )

1146
01:34:56,734 --> 01:34:58,874
(<i> roaring</i> )

1147
01:35:35,438 --> 01:35:37,698
(<i> hissing</i> )

1148
01:35:37,706 --> 01:35:40,406
(<i> guttural growl</i> )

1149
01:35:41,375 --> 01:35:45,405
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1150
01:35:46,445 --> 01:35:50,345
(<i> growling</i> )

1151
01:35:57,687 --> 01:36:00,287
Galen!

1152
01:36:05,727 --> 01:36:08,687
This is Valerian.

1153
01:36:08,696 --> 01:36:11,296
I know, I remember.

1154
01:36:11,298 --> 01:36:14,328
The girl who came to us

1155
01:36:14,334 --> 01:36:16,944
as a boy.

1156
01:36:16,937 --> 01:36:20,797
There's something you must do.

1157
01:36:20,806 --> 01:36:22,066
Anything.

1158
01:36:22,073 --> 01:36:27,843
I want you to
destroy the amulet...

1159
01:36:29,880 --> 01:36:33,920
and me along with it.

1160
01:36:39,621 --> 01:36:42,691
<i> You brought me from the flame.</i>

1161
01:36:42,690 --> 01:36:44,990
You must send me back.

1162
01:36:44,992 --> 01:36:48,492
You'll know the time.

1163
01:36:48,494 --> 01:36:50,134
You must act

1164
01:36:50,128 --> 01:36:55,228
while life is still in me.

1165
01:36:59,437 --> 01:37:03,367
(<i> rumbling</i> )

1166
01:37:30,033 --> 01:37:34,173
(<i> rumbling</i> )

1167
01:37:39,174 --> 01:37:43,514
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1168
01:37:44,578 --> 01:37:48,008
(<i> wind howling</i> )

1169
01:37:48,014 --> 01:37:51,354
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1170
01:38:12,770 --> 01:38:15,900
(<i> wind howling</i> )

1171
01:38:15,906 --> 01:38:17,506
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1172
01:38:17,507 --> 01:38:19,867
(<i> lightning crackling</i> )

1173
01:38:19,876 --> 01:38:23,476
(<i> thunder rumbling</i> )

1174
01:38:32,520 --> 01:38:35,020
There!

1175
01:38:46,666 --> 01:38:50,526
(<i> thunder and lightning stop</i> )

1176
01:39:36,214 --> 01:39:39,684
(<i> dragon roaring</i> )

1177
01:39:42,920 --> 01:39:45,590
(<i> snarling</i> )

1178
01:39:45,589 --> 01:39:48,759
Here, Galen,
do what he said.

1179
01:39:48,758 --> 01:39:50,918
Destroy the amulet.

1180
01:39:50,926 --> 01:39:52,786
Smash it.

1181
01:39:52,794 --> 01:39:54,064
No!

1182
01:39:54,061 --> 01:39:56,091
He said I'd know the time.

1183
01:39:56,096 --> 01:39:59,026
(<i> roaring</i> )

1184
01:40:03,970 --> 01:40:06,500
(<i> roaring</i> )

1185
01:40:12,877 --> 01:40:14,577
(<i> groans</i> )

1186
01:40:35,932 --> 01:40:40,402
(<i> chanting spell in Latin</i> )

1187
01:40:52,747 --> 01:40:54,947
He told you to do it.

1188
01:40:54,949 --> 01:40:56,779
Not yet!

1189
01:41:17,070 --> 01:41:22,140
(<i> thunder rumbling</i> )

1190
01:41:51,103 --> 01:41:53,143
(<i> roaring</i> )

1191
01:42:12,456 --> 01:42:15,516
Galen!

1192
01:42:20,529 --> 01:42:23,559
(<i> dragon roaring in pain</i> )

1193
01:42:50,791 --> 01:42:54,191
(<i> water boiling</i> )

1194
01:43:09,208 --> 01:43:13,238
(<i> sizzling</i> )

1195
01:43:13,244 --> 01:43:17,214
(<i> bird squawking</i> )

1196
01:43:37,934 --> 01:43:42,404
(<i> people singing hymn</i> )

1197
01:43:46,208 --> 01:43:48,368
GREIL:
Let us pray.

1198
01:43:48,376 --> 01:43:52,876
We thank thee, Lord,
for this divine deliverance.

1199
01:43:52,879 --> 01:43:55,609
Verily is thy presence
amongst us

1200
01:43:55,615 --> 01:43:58,215
fully manifest
(<i> hoofbeats approaching</i> )

1201
01:43:58,217 --> 01:44:00,477
in this, thy great work.

1202
01:44:20,537 --> 01:44:23,237
Arise, children of the Lord.

1203
01:44:23,239 --> 01:44:27,409
Forsake forevermore
the pagan mysteries,

1204
01:44:27,409 --> 01:44:29,939
the high superstitions
of the past.

1205
01:44:29,944 --> 01:44:32,144
Rejoice in the true power
of the Christian...

1206
01:44:32,146 --> 01:44:40,746
All hail Casiodorus Rex,
dragon slayer!

1207
01:44:49,128 --> 01:44:51,358
VALERIAN:
You'll miss Ulrich.

1208
01:44:51,363 --> 01:44:53,103
GALEN:
Yes.

1209
01:44:53,098 --> 01:44:54,998
VALERIAN:
And the amulet.

1210
01:44:54,999 --> 01:44:57,099
GALEN:
That, too.

1211
01:44:57,101 --> 01:44:58,171
I don't.

1212
01:44:58,168 --> 01:44:59,498
I'm glad it's gone.

1213
01:44:59,502 --> 01:45:03,242
You may not be a sorcerer,
Galen Brandwardyn,

1214
01:45:03,238 --> 01:45:05,568
but that
doesn't matter.

1215
01:45:05,573 --> 01:45:06,813
Not to me.

1216
01:45:06,807 --> 01:45:07,937
I know.

1217
01:45:07,941 --> 01:45:10,711
I just wish...

1218
01:45:10,710 --> 01:45:11,910
What?

1219
01:45:11,911 --> 01:45:14,481
We had a horse.

1220
01:45:16,080 --> 01:45:19,710
(<i> whinnying</i> )

1221
01:45:30,226 --> 01:45:33,626
(<i> snorting</i> )

1222
01:45:38,266 --> 01:45:42,226
(<i> laughing</i> )

1223
01:45:42,236 --> 01:45:44,836
(<i> whinnying</i> )

